raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.17.0' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-mosaicdata
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/mosaicData_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/mosaicData/mosaicData_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 09375e8fa4e7ca2ca6572f88c199713fa06061d415daa8bbc6d357516aabe013

build:
  noarch: generic
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1002
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:

  host:
    - r-base
  run:
    - r-base

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('mosaicData')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('mosaicData')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=mosaicData
  license: GPL (>= 2)
  summary: Data sets from Project MOSAIC (<http://mosaic-web.org>) used to teach mathematics,
    statistics, computation and modeling.  Funded by the NSF, Project MOSAIC is a community
    of educators working to tie together aspects of quantitative work that students
    in science, technology, engineering and mathematics will need in their professional
    lives, but which are usually taught in isolation, if at all.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - philip-khor
